</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><code>URIElement</code></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Maps a URI element to a siteaccess.<br>This is t=
he default matcher used when choosing <br>URI matching in setup wizard.&nbs=
p;</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>The element number you want to match (startin=
g from 1).</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">ezpublish:
    siteaccess:
        match:
            URIElement: 1</pre>=20
</div>
</div><p><span style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;"><strong>Imp=
ortant:</strong> When using a value &gt; 1, <br>it will concatenate the ele=
ments with _</span></p></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><strong>URI:</strong> <code>/ez=
demo_site/foo/bar</code></p><p><span style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height=
: 13.0pt;"><u>Element number</u>: 1</span><br><span style=3D"font-size: 10.=
0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;"><u>Matched siteaccess</u>: ezdemo_site</span></p>=
<p><u>Element number</u>: 2<br><span style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height=
: 13.0pt;"><u>Matched siteaccess</u>: ezdemo_site_foo&nbsp;</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><code>URIText</code></td>
